The paper deals with the design of transmit waveform and receive filter for MIMO radar, which involves signal processing, optimization, and communication theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The problem formulation also involves system dynamics and control, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper deals with signal processing techniques to maximize the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio, which is a common problem in cs.SP (Signal Processing). The proposed algorithm involves optimization techniques, which is a common theme in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves numerical simulations, which is a common theme in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
